constom\">{{cite web|url=http://www.gnosis.org/library/constom.htm#|title=The Consummation of Thomas the Apostle|publisher=|accessdate=10 May 2015}}</ref>\n\n<!--unused<ref name=\"catholictradition.org\">{{cite web|title = The Life of the Martyred Saint|url = http://www.catholictradition.org/Tradition/apostle-thomas.htm|website = catholictradition.org|accessdate = 2015-09-26}}</ref>-->\n\n<ref name=\"gcatholic.org\">{{cite web|url=http://www.gcatholic.org/churches/italy/0164.htm |title=Co-Cathedral Basilica of St. Thomas the Apostle|website= GCatholic.org |access-date= 2015-01-11}}</ref>\n\n<ref name=\"catholic-saints.info\">{{cite web|url=http://www.catholic-saints.info/patron-saints/patron-saints-countries.htm|title=Patron Saints of Countries|publisher=|accessdate=10 May 2015}}</ref>\n\n<ref name=\"Panjikaran\">{{harvnb|Panjikaran|1926|p=99}} esp. for reference to Pantaenus' Indian visit. Reproduced in ICHC I 'The Nazranies\", ed. George Menachery 1998, pp.&nbsp;277&nbsp;ff.</ref>\n\n<ref name=\"bickell\">Bickell, S. Ephraemi Syri, Caramina Nisibena, Lipsiae, 1866; Monsignor Lamy, S. Ephraemi Syri Hymni et Sermones, (Quarto 4 vols.); Breviary acc. to the Rite of the Church of Antioch of the Syrians, Mosul, 1886\u201396. {{harvnb|Medlycott|1905|pp=21\u201332}} Alias Menachery (Ed.) STCEI, II, pp.&nbsp;18ff.</ref>\n\n<ref name=\"contra arianos\">Homil. XXXII, xi, ''Contra Arianos et de seipso.'' [[Migne]], [[Patrologia Graecae|PG]] 36-228.</ref>\n\n<ref name=\"20c.42.43\">20th Century Discussions : {{harvnb|Medlycott|1905|pp=42-43}}; {{harvnb|Perumalil|1971|pp=43,44}}</ref>\n\n<ref name=\"migne 140\">Migne, P-L 140 1143. (Also see 17. 1131, 17.1133, for his Indian knowledge.)</ref>\n\n<ref name=\"various\">20th Century Discussions : {{harvnb|Medlycott|1905|pp=43-44}}; {{harvnb|Perumalil|1971|pp=44-45}}, Perumalil and Menachery (STCEI I, II), Migne Edns.; Wm. A. Jurgens, Faith of the Early Fathers:etc. History of Christianity-Source Materials by M. K. George, CLS, Madras, 1982 and the Handbook of Source Materials by Wm. G. Young. {{harvnb|Ferroli|1939|pp=71-}}; {{harvnb|Hunt|1920|pp=27, 33, 46\u201350}}; G.T. Mackenzie, i.c.s., \"History of Christianity in Travancore\", in The Travancore State Manual, Vol-II, Edited by Nagam Aiya, Trivandrum 1906, pp.&nbsp;135\u2013233; Menachery, STCEI, I, II.</ref>\n\n<ref name=\"HambyeComes\">20th Century Discussions: {{harvnb|Hambye|1952}}; Comes, S. J., \"Did St. Thomas Really come to India?\", in Menachery (Ed.) STCEI, II. </ref>\n\n<!--\n\n<ref name=\"TOI2006\">{{cite news |last = Ananthakrishnan |first = G. |url = http://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/articleshow/msid-926822,prtpage-1.cms |title=Thomas's visit under doubt |newspaper=Times of India |date=2006-12-26 |access-date=2010-04-25 }}</ref>\n\n<ref name=\"indianchristianity.com\">{{cite web|url=http://www.indianchristianity.com/html/chap4/chapter4a.htm|title=Indian Christianity|publisher=|accessdate=10 May 2015}}</ref>\n\n<ref name=\"NSC Network2\">{{cite web |url = http://nasrani.net/2007/02/13/kerala-syrian-christian-the-tomb-of-the-apostle-persian-church-syond-of-diamper-coonan-cross-oath-divisions/ |title=Kerala Syrian Christian, Apostle in India, The tomb of the Apostle, Persian Church, Syond of Diamper \u2013 Coonan Cross Oath, Subsequent divisions and the Nasrani People |date=2007-02-16|publisher=Nasrani Syrian Christians Network|access-date=2009-10-27}}</ref>\n\n<ref name=\"NSC Network3\">{{cite web |url = http://nasrani.net/2009/07/07/the-thomas-christians-by-placid-podipara/ |title=\u2018The Thomas Christians\u2019 by Placid Podipara |date=2009-07-07 |publisher=Nasrani Syrian Christians Network |access-date=2009-10-27 }}</ref>\n\n<ref name=\"NSC Network4\">{{cite web |url = http://nasrani.net/2008/02/29/analogical-review-on-st-thomas-cross-the-symbol-of-nasranis |title=Analogical review on Saint Thomas Cross- The symbol of Nasranis-Interpretation of the Inscriptions |date=2008-02-29 |publisher=Nasrani Syrian Christians Network |access-date=2009-10-27 }}</ref>\n\n<ref name=\"early christian\">{{cite web |url = http://www.earlychristianwritings.com/actsthomas.html |title=Acts of Thomas |website = Earlychristianwritings.com |date=2006-02-02 |access-date=2010-04-25 }}</ref>\n\n<ref name=\"Faith\">Faith and Character of Apostle Thomas by Dr. [[Matthew Vellanickal]] and many other articles in ''St. Thomas Christian Encyclopaedia'' ed. Prof. George Menachery, Vol.2, 1973.</ref>\n\n-->\n\n}}\n\n===Sources===\n{{refbegin|2|indent=yes}}\n\n*{{cite book|ref=harv|last=Andrade|first=Nathanael J. |title=The Journey of Christianity to India in Late Antiquity: Networks and the Movement of Culture|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=UrpQDwAAQBAJ|date= 2018|publisher=University Press|location=Cambridge |isbn=978-1-108-41912-3}}\n\n*{{cite web|url=http://nasrani.net/2010/10/09/saint-thomas-cross-a-religio-cultural-logo-of-saint-thomas-christians/ |title=Saint Thomas Cross- A Religio Cultural Logo of Saint Thomas Christians |work=Nasrani.net |date=17 February 2019 |accessdate=2012-06-16|ref=harv|first=M Thomas |last=Antony}}\n\n*{{cite book|ref=harv|author=Arnobius of Sicca|authorlink=Arnobius|translator=George E. McCracken|title=The Case Against the Pagans|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=_0BKFcTWD7gC&pg=PA125|volume=Volume 1|year=1949|publisher=Paulist Press|isbn=978-0-8091-0248-8}}\n\n*{{cite news |last=Arraf|first=Jane|date=31 March 2018|title=Iraq's Christians Remain Displaced This Easter|url=https://www.npr.org/2018/03/31/598503561/iraqs-christians-remain-displaced-this-easter|work=[[NPR]]|access-date=18 May 2018|ref=harv}}\n\n*{{cite book|ref=harv|last=Bays|first=Daniel H. |title=A New History of Christianity in China|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=mxhnByM5KhgC|date= 2011|publisher=John Wiley & Sons|isbn=978-1-4051-5954-8}}\n\n*{{cite book|ref=harv|last=Brown|first=Leslie W. |authorlink=Leslie W. Brown|title=The Indian Christians of St Thomas, an Account of the Ancient Syrian Church 