ration]]\n[[Category:Conservation biology]]\n[[Category:Glossaries of biology|Invasion biology terms]]\n", "name_user": "Iridescent", "label": "safe", "comment": "\u2192\u200eReferences:Cleanup andtypo fixing,typo(s) fixed: 315-339 \u2192 315\u2013339, 555-58 \u2192 555\u201358 (3)", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Glossary_of_invasion_biology_terms"}
{"title_page": "Evander Holyfield vs. James Toney", "text_new": "{{Infobox Boxingmatch\n|fight date=October 4, 2003\n|Fight Name=The War on October 4\n|location=[[Mandalay Bay Events Center]] in [[Paradise, Nevada]]\n|image=[[File:Holyfield vs Toney.jpg|250px]]\n|fighter1=[[Evander Holyfield]]\n|nickname1=\"The Real Deal\"\n|record1=38\u20136\u20132\n|height1=6'2\"\n|weight1=219 lbs\n|style1=Orthodox\n|hometown1=[[Atlanta|Atlanta Georgia]], [[United States|U.S.]]\n|recognition1=Former<br>4-time heavyweight champion\n|fighter2=[[James Toney]]\n|nickname2=\"Lights Out\"\n|record2=66\u20134\u20132\n|hometown2=[[Grand Rapids, Michigan]], U.S.\n|height2=5'10\"\n|weight2=217 lbs\n|style2=Orthodox\n|recognition2=[[International Boxing Federation|IBF]]<br>Cruiserweight Champion\n|titles=None\n|result= Toney defeats Holyfield by TKO in round nine\n}}\n'''[[Evander Holyfield]] vs. [[James Toney]]''', billed as \"'''The War on October 4'''\", was a professional boxing match contested on October 4, 2003.\n\n==Background==\nIn June 2003, it was announced that former 4-time world heavyweight champion Evander Holyfield would face reigning [[International Boxing Federation|IBF]] cruiserweight champion James Toney in a non-title bout set for October 4, 2003.<ref>[https://www.upi.com/Sports_News/2003/06/24/Holyfield-to-fight-James-Toney/45321056481653/ Holyfield to fight James Toney], UPI article, 2003-06-24, Retrieved on 2020-04-07</ref>\n\nHolyfield's previous fight had been a loss to [[Chris Byrd]] in an IBF heavyweight title fight. Following the loss, Holyfield had entered negotiations with promoter [[Don King (boxing promoter)|Don King]] to face then-[[World Boxing Association|WBA]] heavyweight champion [[Roy Jones Jr.]] Jones' promoter claimed Holyfield was offered a $10 million purse, but negotiations fell through when Holyfield demanded an additional $2 million added on because he claimed King owed him such. After the proposed Holyfield\u2013Jones fight fell through, Holyfield instead reached an agreement to face Toney<ref>[https://www.nytimes.com/2003/06/25/sports/boxing-toney-and-holyfield-in-heavyweight-bout.html Toney and Holyfield In Heavyweight Bout], NY Times article, 2002-06-02, Retrieved on 2020-04-08</ref> Toney had won the IBF cruiserweight title in April by defeating [[Vassiliy Jirov]], giving him his first major title since 1994 and making him a 3-division world champion as he had previously captured titles in both the middleweight and super middleweight divisions. Toney and his promoter Dan Goossen had agreed that if Toney beat Jirov for the cruiserweight title, then he could \"do what he wanted.\" After doing so, Toney then decided to move up to the heavyweight division.<ref>[https://www.espn.com/sports/boxing/news/story?id=2368339 Was Toney a 'slimmed-down' heavyweight all along?], ESPN article, 2006-03-14, Retrieved on 2020-04-08</ref>\n\n==The fight==\nHolyfield got off to a good start in the fight, winning two of the first three rounds on two of the judge's scorecards and all three on the other judge's scorecards. However, from the fourth round on, Toney would dominate Holyfield, punishing him with a series of powerful combinations and left hooks and winning every round from then on. After punishing Holyfield for 5+ rounds, Toney was finally able to breakthrough with a knockdown in round nine after landing left hook to the body caused Holyfield to collapse to the mat. Holyfield would get back up, but his trainer [[Don Turner]] decided to stop the fight by throwing in the towel, automatically giving Toney the victory by technical knockout at 1:42 of the round.<ref>[https://www.upi.com/Sports_News/2003/10/05/Toney-gets-TKO-of-Holyfield/86891065335355/?ur3=1 Toney gets TKO of Holyfield], UPI article, 2003-10-05, Retrieved on 2020-04-06</ref>\n\nThough Holyfield admitted that \"Toney did beat me up\" and there were calls for his retirement following consecutive defeats, Holyfield decided to put retirement off, stating \"No, I'm not going to retire, I'm going back to the drawing board.\"<ref>[https://www.espn.com/boxing/news/2003/1004/1630682.html Holyfield's career may be over], ESPN article, 2003-10-05, Retrieved on 2020-04-08</ref>\n\n==Fight card==\n{| class=\"toccolours\" style=\"font-size: 85%;\"\n|-\n! style=\"background:#e6e8fa; color:#000; text-align:center;\"| Weight Class\n! style=\"background:#e6e8fa; color:#000; text-align:center;\"| Weight\n! style=\"background:#e6e8fa; color:#000; text-align:center;\"|\n! style=\"background:#e6e8fa; color:#000; text-align:center;\"| vs.\n! style=\"background:#e6e8fa; color:#000; text-align:center;\"|\n! style=\"background:#e6e8fa; color:#000; text-align:center;\"| Method\n! style=\"background:#e6e8fa; color:#000; text-align:center;\"| Round\n! style=\"background:#e6e8fa; color:#000; text-align:center;\"| Notes\n|-\n|Heavyweight\n|200+ lbs.\n|'''[[James Toney]]'''\n|def.\n|[[Evander Holyfield]]\n|align=center|TKO\n|align=center|9/12\n|-\n|Super Featherweight\n|126 lbs.\n|'''[[Joel Casamayor]]''' \n|def.\n|[[Diego Corrales]]\n|align=center|TKO\n|align=center|6/12\n|{{ref|Joel Casamayor vs. Diego Corrales|Note 1}}\n|-\n|Bantamweight\n|118 lbs.\n|'''[[Cruz Carbajal]]''' (c)\n|def\n|Gerardo Espinoza\n|align=center|TKO\n|align=center|8/12\n|{{ref|Cruz Carbajal vs. Gerardo Espinoza|Note 2}}\n|-\n|Middleweight\n|160 lbs.\n|'''[[Keith Holmes (boxer)|Keith Holmes]]'''\n|def\n|Jason Papillion\n|align=center|TKO\n|align=center|8/8\n|}\n{{note|Joel Casamayor vs. Diego Corrales|Note 1|For [[International Boxing Association (professional)|IBA]] Super Featherweight title}}<br>{{note|Cruz Carbajal vs. Gerardo Espinoza|Note 2|For [[World Boxing Organization|WBO]] Bantamweight title}}\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n{{Evander Holyfield}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Holyfield, Toney}}\n[[Category:2003 in boxing]]\n[[Category:Boxing in Las Vegas]]\n[[Category:Boxing on Showtime]]\n[[Category:Boxing matches involving Evander Holyfield|Toney]]\n[[Category:October 2003 sports events in the United States]]\n", "text_old": "{{Infobox Boxingmatch\n|fight date=October 4, 2003\n|Fight Name=The War on October 4\n|location=[[Mandalay Bay Events Center]] in [[Paradise, Nevada]]\n|image=[[File:Holyfield vs Toney.jpg|250px]]\n|fighter1=[[Evander Holyfield]]\n|nickname1=\"The Real Deal\"\n|record1=38\u20136\u20132\n|height1=6'2\"\n|weight1=219 lbs\n|style1=Orthodox\n|hometown1=[[Atlanta|Atlanta Georgia]], [[United States|U.S.]]\n|recognition1=Former<br>4-time heavyweight champion\n|fighter2=[[James Toney]]\n|nickname2=\"Lights Out\"\n|record2=66\u20134\u20132\n|hometown2=[[Grand Rapids, Michigan]], U.S.\n|height2=5'10\"\n|weight2=217 lbs\n|style2=Orthodox\n|recognition2=[[International Boxing Federation|IBF]]<br>Cruiserweight Champion\n|titles=None\n|result= Toney defeats Holyfield by TKO in round nine\n}}\n'''[[Evander Holyfield]] vs. [[James Toney]]''', billed as \"'''The War on October 4'''\", was a professional boxing match contested on October 4, 2003.\n\n==Background==\nIn June 2003, it was announced that former 4-time world heavyweight champion Evander Holyfield would face reigning [[International Boxing Federation|IBF]] cruiserweight champion James Toney in a non-title bout set for October 4, 2003.<ref>[https://www.upi.com/Sports_News/2003/06/24/Holyfield-to-fight-James-Toney/45321056481653/ Holyfield to fight James Toney], UPI article, 2003-06-24, Retrieved on 2020-04-07</ref> \n\nHolyfield's previous fight had been a loss to [[Chris Byrd]] in a IBF heavyweight title fight. Following the loss, Holyfield had entered negotiations with promoter [[Don King (boxing promoter)|Don King]] to face then-[[World Boxing Association|WBA]] heavyweight champion [[Roy Jones Jr.]] Jones' promoter claimed Holyfield was offered a $10 million purse, but negotiations fell through when Holyfield demanded an additional $2 million added on because he claimed King owed him such. After the proposed Holyfield\u2013Jones fight fell through, Holyfield instead reached an agreement to face Toney<ref>[https://www.nytimes.com/2003/06/25/sports/boxing-toney-and-holyfield-in-heavyweight-bout.html Toney and Holyfield In Heavyweight Bout], NY Times article, 2002-06-02, Retrieved on 2020-04-08</ref> Toney had won the IBF cruiserweight title in April by defeating [[Vassiliy Jirov]], giving him his first major title since 1994 and making him a 3-division world champion as he had previously captured titles in both the middleweight and super middleweight divisions. Toney and his promoter Dan Goossen had agreed that if Toney beat Jirov for the cruiserweight title, then he could \"do what he wanted.\" After doing so, Toney then decided to move up to the heavyweight division.<ref>[https://www.espn.com/sports/boxing/news/story?id=2368339 Was Toney a 'slimmed-down' heavyweight all along?], ESPN article, 2006-03-14, Retrieved on 2020-04-08</ref> \n\n==The fight==\nHolyfield got off to a good start in the fight, winning two of the first three rounds on two of the judge's scorecards and all three on the other judge's scorecards. However, from the fourth round on, Toney would dominate Holyfield, punishing him with a series of powerful combinations and left hooks and winning every round from then on. After punishing Holyfield for 5+ rounds, Toney was finally able to breakthrough with a knockdown in round nine after landing left hook to the body caused Holyfield to collapse to the mat. Holyfield would get back up, but his trainer [[Don Turner]] decided to stop the fight by throwing in the towel, automatically giving Toney the victory by technical knockout at 1:42 of the round.<ref>[https://www.upi.com/Sports_News/2003/10/05/Toney-gets-TKO-of-Holyfield/86891065335355/?ur3=1 Toney gets TKO of Holyfield], UPI article, 2003-10-05, Retrieved on 2020-04-06</ref>\n\nThough Holyfield admitted that \"Toney did beat me up\" and there were calls for his retirement following consecutive defeats, Holyfield decided to put retirement off, stating \"No, I'm not going to retire, I'm going back to the drawing board.\"<ref>[https://www.espn.com/boxing/news/2003/1004/1630682.html Holyfield's career may be over], ESPN article, 2003-10-05, Retrieved on 2020-04-08</ref>  \n\n==Fight card==\n{| class=\"toccolours\" style=\"font-size: 85%;\"\n|-\n! style=\"background:#e6e8fa; color:#000; text-align:center;\"| Weight Class\n! style=\"background:#e6e8fa; color:#000; text-align:center;\"| Weight\n! style=\"background:#e6e8fa; color:#000; text-align:center;\"|\n! style=\"background:#e6e8fa; color:#000; text-align:center;\"| vs.\n! style=\"background:#e6e8fa; color:#000; text-align:center;\"|\n! style=\"background:#e6e8fa; color:#000; text-align:center;\"| Method\n! style=\"background:#e6e8fa; color:#000; text-align:center;\"| Round\n! style=\"background:#e6e8fa; color:#000; text-align:center;\"| Notes\n|-\n|Heavyweight\n|200+ lbs.\n|'''[[James Toney]]'''\n|def.\n|[[Evander Holyfield]]\n|align=center|TKO\n|align=center|9/12\n|-\n|Super Featherweight\n|126 lbs.\n|'''[[Joel Casamayor]]''' \n|def.\n|[[Diego Corrales]]\n|align=center|TKO\n|align=center|6/12\n|{{ref|Joel Casamayor vs. Diego Corrales|Note 1}}\n|-\n|Bantamweight\n|118 lbs.\n|'''[[Cruz Carbajal]]''' (c)\n|def\n|Gerardo Espinoza\n|align=center|TKO\n|align=center|8/12\n|{{ref|Cruz Carbajal vs. Gerardo Espinoza|Note 2}}\n|-\n|Middleweight\n|160 lbs.\n|'''[[Keith Holmes (boxer)|Keith Holmes]]'''\n|def\n|Jason Papillion\n|align=center|TKO\n|align=center|8/8\n|}\n{{note|Joel Casamayor vs. Diego Corrales|Note 1|For [[International Boxing Association (professional)|IBA]] Super Featherweight title}}<br>{{note|Cruz Carbajal vs. Gerardo Espinoza|Note 2|For [[World Boxing Organization|WBO]] Bantamweight title}}\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Holyfield, Toney}}\n{{Evander Holyfield}}\n[[Category:2003 in boxing]]\n[[Category:Boxing in Las Vegas]]\n[[Category:Boxing on Showtime]]\n[[Category:Boxing matches involving Evander Holyfield|Toney]]\n[[Category:October 2003 sports events in the United States]]\n", "name_user": "Nat965", "label": "safe", "comment": "ApplyGen fix(es),typo(s) fixed: a IBF \u2192 an IBF", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Evander_Holyfield_vs._James_Toney"}
